[2026-07-13T17:35:00.559Z] [INFO]           "prompt": "In this repository (/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954), I'm investigating issue #681: a natural-language file-creation request (e.g. \"Create a file named hello.txt with content hello world\") causes the server to emit a `read` tool_call on the nonexistent target file instead of a `write` tool_call, even when both read and write tools are advertised. This is in the OpenAI-compatible chat completions endpoint (`POST /api/openai/v1/chat/completions`), agent mode (FORMAL_AI_AGENT_MODE=1).\n\nFind and report the exact file paths and line numbers for the code responsible for:\n1. The OpenAI chat completions endpoint handler that produces tool_calls.\n2. The \"planner\" or intent-classification logic that decides which tool (read vs write) to emit for a natural-language request.\n3. Any code matching keywords like: \"tool_call\", \"write\", \"read\", \"planner\", \"intent\", \"agent mode\", \"advertise\", \"capability\", the phrase \"I can read\" or \"when the client advertises a file read tool\".\n4. Existing tests covering tool_call emission / intent classification.\n\nDo a thorough, medium-breadth search. Report a concise list of file:line references with a one-line description of each, so I can compile them into a case-study data folder. Do NOT modify any files."
[2026-07-13T17:35:00.559Z] [INFO]         },
[2026-07-13T17:35:00.559Z] [INFO]         "caller": {
