[2026-07-13T17:37:42.987Z] [INFO]         "text": "I have a complete picture of the code responsible for this bug. Here is my report.\n\n## Root cause summary\n\nFor the prompt \"Create a file named hello.txt with content hello world\", the planner routes it to the **file-read** recipe (emitting a `read` tool_call) instead of the file-creation/write recipe. Two things cause this:\n\n1. `has_file_read_intent` matches on the substring `\"content\"` — which appears in \"with **content** hello world\" — so the prompt is misclassified as a read.\n2. In `plan_chat_step`, the file-read check runs *before* the general file-creation planner, so the read interception wins even though a write path exists.\n\n(Secondarily, even if it reached the write planner, `extract_target` requires the word before the filename to be one of `file/in/create/…`, but here the preceding word is \"named\", so the write path would also fail to fire.)\n\n## 1. OpenAI chat completions endpoint handler (produces tool_calls)\n\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/server.rs:178` — route `POST /v1/chat/completions | /api/openai/v1/chat/completions`, calls `create_chat_completion_with_solver_and_memory`.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/protocol.rs:586` — `create_chat_completion_with_solver_and_memory`, dispatches on `agentic_outcome(...)`.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/protocol.rs:638` — `agentic_outcome`: checks agent mode / permissions, then calls `plan_chat_step` (line 669) to get the plan.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/protocol.rs:687-715` — `chat_completion_from_plan`: turns an `AgenticPlan::ToolCalls` into OpenAI `tool_calls` with `finish_reason:\"tool_calls\"`.\n\n## 2. Planner / intent-classification (decides read vs write)\n\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:117` — `plan_chat_step`, the top-level router.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:205-207` — file-read recipe check, **runs before** the general write planner. This is where the misroute happens.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:220-221` — `compose_general_change_plan` fallback (the write path), reached only if file-read didn't match.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:177` — `file_read_task_for`, the read-intent classifier.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:225-242` — `has_file_read_intent`, the keyword list containing `\"content\"` (line 229) that false-positives on \"with content …\".\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:69-107` — `plan_direct_file_read`, emits the `read` tool_call (line 95-96) or the \"I can read …\" message (line 106).\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/general_planner.rs:67` — `compose_general_change_plan` (write plan).\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/general_planner.rs:108-123` — `extract_target`; note the preceding-word allowlist `[\"file\",\"файл\",\"in\",\"в\",\"create\",\"создай\"]` (line 120) excludes \"named\".\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/general_planner.rs:125-143` — `extract_content`, the content markers (` with content `, etc.).\n\n## 3. Capability / tool-advertisement code and the \"I can read\" / \"advertises a file read tool\" phrases\n\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:79-102` — `Capability` enum (Read/Write/Run/Search/Fetch) and capability keys (`tool:capability:read`, `tool:capability:write`).\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:110` — `tool_capability`, classifies an advertised tool name into a `Capability`.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:791-826` — tool-name → capability mapping conventions (`read`, `write`/`write_file`, `edit`, `patch`, …).\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:106` — literal `\"I can read \\`{path}\\` when the client advertises a file read tool or a shell tool.\"`\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:124` / `:172` — related \"when the client advertises …\" fallback messages.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:274` — the run/shell analog: \"I can run … when the client advertises a shell tool …\".\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/solver_handlers/natural_language_tools.rs:224-250` — `require_tool_permission` / capability-gating (`tool:{tool_name}`, agent-mode requirement).\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/src/protocol.rs:79-88` — `requests_tool_execution` (whether client advertised tools); `requested_tool_names` used to build `tool_names`.\n\n## 4. Existing tests covering tool_call emission / intent classification\n\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/tests/unit/issue_627.rs:44` — `direct_file_read_prompts_emit_read_tool_calls` (asserts `call.tool == \"read\"`); also lines 102/133/158/185/213 assert `read` emission through the endpoint. This is the closest test to the bug and where a write-vs-read regression test would belong.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/tests/unit/agentic_general_planner.rs:44` — `general_plan_is_emitted_before_execution` and the create-file cases (EN_TASK \"Create file notes/general-demo.txt containing …\"); confirms the write path works only with the \"file\"/\"containing\" phrasing, not \"named\"/\"with content\".\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/tests/unit/agentic_coding.rs:156,297,468,490,500` — general `plan_chat_step` tool_call assertions.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/tests/integration/issue_624_agent_mode.rs` — agent-mode gating over the chat endpoint.\n- `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954/tests/integration/openai_chat_streaming.rs` — OpenAI chat completions streaming surface.\n\nOne note: the working directory you launched me in (`dev/log/issues/681/pulls/684/raw-data/`) already contains issue/PR JSON fixtures (`issue-681.json`, `pr-684.json`, `issue-680-umbrella.json`, `related-prs-search.json`) for the case study."
