[2026-07-13T17:40:33.486Z] [INFO]           "command": "cd /tmp/gh-issue-solver-1783963932954\ncat > /tmp/pr684-body.md <<'EOF'\n## 📚 Data log for issue #681\n\nThis PR compiles the data related to\n[issue #681](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/681)\n(*a file-creation request emits a `read` tool_call on the nonexistent target\ninstead of `write`*) into `dev/log/issues/681/pulls/684/`, mirroring the\nstructure established by PR #683 for the umbrella issue #680.\n\n### 📋 Issue reference\nRelates to #681 · umbrella #680\n\n### 📂 What was collected\n\n```\ndev/log/issues/681/pulls/684/\n├── README.md            ← index + issue summary + root cause + reproduction\n├── issue/               ← issue #681 JSON, rendered, comments\n├── pull/                ← PR #684 JSON, rendered, diff, comments, reviews\n├── related/             ← umbrella #680 + siblings 602/604/607/628/671 + PR search\n└── code/                ← root-cause source snapshots @ v0.282.0 + code-references.md\n```\n\n### 🔎 Root cause identified (see `code/code-references.md`)\n\n1. `has_file_read_intent` (`src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:229`) matches the\n   keyword **`\"content\"`**, which appears in *\"with **content** hello world\"*, so\n   a write request is classified as a read intent.\n2. `plan_chat_step` (`src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:205-207`) checks the\n   file-read recipe **before** the general write/create planner, so the read\n   interception wins.\n3. Secondary: `extract_target` (`src/agentic_coding/general_planner.rs:120`)\n   only accepts a filename after `file/in/create/…` — not after **\"named\"** — so\n   the write path would also miss this phrasing even if reached.\n\n### ✅ Scope\nData-collection only — no source behavior changed.\nEOF\ngh pr edit 684 --repo link-assistant/formal-ai \\\n  --title \"docs(issue-681): compile issue/PR/related data into dev/log\" \\\n  --body-file /tmp/pr684-body.md 2>&1 | tail -3",
