[2026-07-13T17:40:59.534Z] [INFO]         "text": "Done. I've collected and compiled all data related to issue #681 into `./dev/log/issues/681/pulls/684/`, committed it, pushed to the branch, and updated PR #684.\n\n## What was collected\n\nI mirrored the proven structure of PR #683 (which did the same for the umbrella issue #680):\n\n```\ndev/log/issues/681/pulls/684/\n├── README.md                    ← index, issue summary, root cause, reproduction\n├── issue/    issue #681 JSON + rendered + comments\n├── pull/     PR #684 JSON + rendered + diff + conversation/review comments + reviews\n├── related/  umbrella #680 (JSON/md/comments) + siblings 602/604/607/628/671 + related-PR search\n└── code/     code-references.md, endpoint-dispatch-excerpts.md, and read-only\n              source snapshots @ v0.282.0 (planner.rs, file_read.rs, general_planner.rs,\n              change_request.rs, driver.rs, natural_language_tools.rs) + closest tests\n```\n\n## Root cause pinpointed while gathering the `code/` snapshots\n\nThe issue is a **write→read misroute**, caused by two compounding defects (documented in `code/code-references.md`):\n\n1. **`has_file_read_intent` false-positives on `\"content\"`** — `src/agentic_coding/file_read.rs:229` lists `\"content\"` as a read keyword, and *\"with **content** hello world\"* trips it, classifying a write request as a read.\n2. **Read is checked before write** — `plan_chat_step` (`src/agentic_coding/planner.rs:205-207`) runs the file-read recipe before the general write/create planner, so the read interception wins.\n3. **Secondary:** `extract_target` (`general_planner.rs:120`) only accepts a filename after `file/in/create/…`, not after **\"named\"**, so the write path would also miss this phrasing.\n\n## State\n\n- Commit `5735be90` pushed to `issue-681-5dc4419f2eb7`, working tree clean.\n- PR #684 retitled to `docs(issue-681): compile issue/PR/related data into dev/log` with an updated description: https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/684\n\nI left the PR in **draft** — this task was data collection only; no source behavior was changed and the actual fix isn't implemented yet (matching how the sibling PR #683 remains draft)."
